    ('EDBE 8G22', 'Teaching Communications Tech I (gr 11-12)', 'Examination of Ontario Ministry, board and school curriculum documents and other resources. In-depth study of the communication industry; the technical knowledge and skills required to teach component areas such as television/video production, art, broadcasting, photography, web communication, print/graphic production at the senior level. Exploration of secondary and post-secondary education pathways and career opportunities.', 'D10', '', ' ', 'ASY', 'Notes: Open to students admitted to Technological Educati on program. this course may be offered in multiple modes of delivery. The method of delivery will be listed on the academic timetable, in the applicable term.', 'Instructor: Sheahan, Mike', 'Section: 1'),
